The ozone layer is a layer of the atmosphere that protects the Earth from the sun's harmful ultraviolet rays. The ozone hole was discovered in 1985 by scientists from the British Antarctic Survey. The ozone hole is caused by chlorofluorocarbons (CFCs) and other chemicals that are released into the atmosphere. These chemicals are released into the atmosphere by humans.
